<CENTER>
<H1><HR><I>Manual Reference Pages &nbsp;-&nbsp;</I><NOBR>CCS-LOADPOLICY (8)</NOBR><HR></H1>
</CENTER>
<!-- .SH "NAME" -->
<A name=>

     <H3>NAME</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
ccs-loadpolicy - load TOMOYO Linux policy manually
<!-- .SH "SYNOPSIS" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=1>

     <H3>SYNOPSIS</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .B ccs-loadpolicy [options] -->
<B>ccs-loadpolicy [options]</B> <!-- .sp -->
<P>
<!-- .B ccs-loadpolicy [options] <remote_ip:remote_port> -->
<B>ccs-loadpolicy [options] &lt;remote_ip:remote_port&gt;</B> <!-- .SH "DESCRIPTION" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=>

     <H3>DESCRIPTION</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
This program reads TOMOYO Linux policy from standard input and loads it into the kernel.
<!-- .SH "OPTIONS" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=>

     <H3>OPTIONS</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>-e</B>
<!-- .RS 4 -->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Append to <I>/proc/ccs/exception_policy</I>.
<!-- .RE -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<B>-ef</B>
<!-- .RS 4 -->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Overwrite to <I>/proc/ccs/exception_policy</I>.
<!-- .RE -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<B>-d</B>
<!-- .RS 4 -->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Append to <I>/proc/ccs/domain_policy</I>.
<!-- .RE -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<B>-df</B>
<!-- .RS 4 -->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Overwrite to <I>/proc/ccs/domain_policy</I>.
<!-- .RE -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<B>-m</B>
<!-- .RS 4 -->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Append to <I>/proc/ccs/manager</I>.
<!-- .RE -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<B>-p</B>
<!-- .RS 4 -->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Append to <I>/proc/ccs/profile</I>.
<!-- .RE -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<B>-s</B>
<!-- .RS 4 -->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Append to <I>/proc/ccs/stat</I>.
<!-- .RE -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<B>&lt;remote_ip:remote_port&gt;</B>
<!-- .RS 4 -->
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Instead of writing to local kernel memory, write to an agent waiting at port <I>&lt;remote_port&gt;</I> on IP address <I>&lt;remote_ip&gt;</I>.
<!-- .RE -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<!-- .SH "EXAMPLES" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=>

     <H3>EXAMPLES</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<!-- .B Add \&"file read proc:/meminfo\&" to acl_group 0: -->
<B>Add  file read proc:/meminfo to acl_group 0:</B> <!-- .nf -->
<PRE>
echo "acl_group 0 file read proc:/meminfo" | ccs-loadpolicy -e
<!-- .fi -->
</PRE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<!-- .B Remove \&"file read proc:/meminfo\&" from acl_group 0: -->
<B>Remove  file read proc:/meminfo from acl_group 0:</B> <!-- .nf -->
<PRE>
echo "delete acl_group 0 file read proc:/meminfo" | ccs-loadpolicy -e
<!-- .fi -->
</PRE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<!-- .B Add \&"file execute /sbin/init\&" to <kernel> domain: -->
<B>Add  file execute /sbin/init to &lt;kernel&gt; domain:</B> <!-- .nf -->
<PRE>
( echo "&lt;kernel&gt;"; echo "file execute /sbin/init" ) | ccs-loadpolicy -d
<!-- .fi -->
</PRE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<!-- .B Replace currently loaded domain policy with \&"/etc/ccs/domain_policy.conf\&": -->
<B>Replace currently loaded domain policy with  /etc/ccs/domain_policy.conf :</B> <!-- .nf -->
<PRE>
ccs-loadpolicy -df &lt; /etc/ccs/domain_policy.conf
<!-- .fi -->
</PRE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<!-- .B Append \&"/etc/ccs/192.168.1.1/domain_policy.conf to 192.168.1.1:10000: -->
<B>Append /etc/ccs/192.168.1.1/domain_policy.conf to 192.168.1.1:10000:</B> <!-- .nf -->
<PRE>
ccs-loadpolicy -d 192.168.1.1:10000 &lt; /etc/ccs/192.168.1.1/domain_policy.conf
<!-- .fi -->
</PRE>
<!-- .PP -->
<P>
<!-- .B Remove \&"/usr/sbin/ccs-queryd\&" from \&"/proc/ccs/manager\&": -->
<B>Remove  /usr/sbin/ccs-queryd from  /proc/ccs/manager :</B> <!-- .nf -->
<PRE>
echo "delete /usr/sbin/ccs-queryd" | ccs-loadpolicy -m
<!-- .fi -->
</PRE>
<!-- .SH "NOTES" -->
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A name=>

     <H3>NOTES</H3>

</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
Before this program can be invoked, it must be registered in <I>/proc/ccs/manager</I>. After initializing policy, this is usually as simple as rebooting the system.
